This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques applied to social media data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning models, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-task learning, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves data analysis, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves the use of a newly-created dataset, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound).
